01/09/2004
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- SFOR personnel have detained a second alleged supporter of fugitive war crimes indictee Radovan Karadzic. The Srpsko Sarajevo Public Security Centre confirmed Tuesday (31 August) that Veljko Borovina, 34, a chauffeur, has been arrested. He is the cousin of Milovan Cicko Bjelica, who was picked up early Tuesday in Sokolac, Republika Srpska. The two are described as close associates of Karadzic. (Dnevni avaz, Nezavisne novine - 01/09/04; Pincom.info - 31/08/04)
